rs who work in concert with them. Contributors: Catherine Graham, Subhasri Ghosh, Jon Gordon, Maroussia Hajdukowski-Ahmed, Agnes Kramer-Hamstra, Mazen Masri, Jean McDonald, and Pavithra Narayanan.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCreation (Literary, artistic, etc.)vCross-cultural studies. 0aIndigenous peoplesvCross-cultural studies. 0aInternally displaced personsvCross-cultural studies. 0aRefugeesvCross-cultural studies. 0aResilience (Personality trait)vCross-cultural studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies / Displaced Peoples / Criticism.1 aColeman, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGhosh, Subhasri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlanville, Erin Goheen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGordon, Jon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraham, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHajdukowski-Ahmed, Maroussia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasan, Wafaa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKramer-Hamstra, Agnes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKramer-Hamstra, Agnes, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMasri, Mazen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMc Donald, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcDonald, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNarayanan, Pavithra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gr